3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with probabilistic systems modeled as Markov Decision Processes, which is a key area of research in systems and control. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper mentions that probabilistic systems are prevalent in robotics, indicating that the paper may be relevant to the robotics community. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a framework that uses compositional model checking to alleviate the state space explosion, which is a key area of research in data structures and algorithms.
